column5: Is that a fire truck?
Is that a fire truck?  U-Haul.
Check out the silver car , did it roll down the street or what ? If it did good old mother nature can even park cars !
Wow!
Storm is in Mississauga now
As Ron White says: It's not that the wind is blowin'. It's what the wind is blowin'.   Not safe for work video (language):  http://shelby.tv/video/vimeo/28271386/ron-white-hurricane
No Twisters in Streetville but my flip flops did get soaked and made for some slippy walking.
hope everyone is alright...
Something messed up is passing through us here.....
TORNADO WARNINGS HAVE BEEN LIFTED

along with a lot of roofs, trees, and at least one truck. This place has better weather coverage than the weathernetwork. hope everyone is OK -  I was in one in Carnarvon a half dozen years ago. Incredible what 90 seconds of wind and water can do.
It got a little nasty here in the wick, nothing i havent seen before. Hope everything is ok in the north end
After the Barrie tornado in '85 black clouds/skies don't concern me as much as green ones do.
FRIG...just rolled thru here ...heads up Roy  Sky is doin crazy stuff

we had a funnel cloud here in grand valley but it did not touchdown.  hope everyone's ok in angus.  i think that first pic you posted drifter is from last year, saw that one form around kenilworth/mount forest and then head east along 9 with me behind it. i think that photo was taken by dave patrick, a local stormchaser.  not sure why its being reused.

Quite a number of houses damaged in the Gold Park subdivision on the 5th line, roofs and second story gone on one row of houses,  neighbouring streets had siding and shingles missing.  Other local areas had various damage. 12foot springboks shed is gone along with some stuff,  he's alright, little bit shell shocked, back at home with us for now.  It rolled through here at 5pm, man what a blast of rain and wind.  Hope nobody was hurt.
Glad you're ok man.
Ya , glad you guys are alright !
Talked to my sis around 9 last night. She was showing a house on the same street as that U haul that was turned over. She was scared to death.

That was a whole lot of bull crap...    Back yard is completely screwed  100 feet to the south and my roof would have been gone. Most of my ice fishing and camping gear in my shed has been destroyed...  Unreal could have been way worse though.
That sucks man, hopefully you can get your stuff back together soon.
Holy crappy camera work Batman!!!!
Holy crappy camera work Batman!!!!   When I starting watching it Dave,I was saying,drop the ^$& camera and see if anyone needs help.
Global says it's confirmed it was a tornado that hit Angus.  Hope Fisherman is OK
Just heard that there is Major damage to some homes in the Angus area  The confirmed that a Tornado was on the ground in Angus
I live just west of Angus , and I can confirm it was really bad !!!!
the warning area just was updated now includes City of Hamilton  TORNADO WARNINGS currently in effect as of 5:40 p.m. EST
Calm here again. Sun is trying to peek through. Lots of wires down around the simcoe area.  Waiting to hear back from my sister.
35 minutes ago in Angus.
Owen Sound
35 minutes ago in Angus.     That would be the south east section of the town.  Hope no one was seriously hurt.
Owen Sound     Thats HUGE.
If you're in the Caledon/Vaughn area seek shelter now!!!!    Take shelter with this storm. Multiple homes damaged. Large Tornadoes reported.
That would be the south east section of the town.  Hope no one was seriously hurt.  Damage in Angus
FYI There is a gnarly cell heading for Hamiton another in Brampton and a pair in the Caledon and Newmarket areas.. Keep your eyes on the skies.
I heard it was bad in Angus , but not that bad !
Holly crap Dave.    AND WE JUST DEALT WITH THIS
That's like every summer afternoon in Florida!!!
Crazy here in Richmond Hill right now!!!
That's like every summer afternoon in Florida!!!  Water slides every day eh.  If the traffic wasnt so bad,I would take the tube out and slide down Essa hill.
Aurora as well a friend is saying,nasty!!
Crazy here in Richmond Hill right now!!!  Keep your eyes on the skies. This is a bad cell.

Just heard that there is Major damage to some homes in the Angus area  Yup, something did some really bad damage out that way.  I just took a drive, trees down everywhere, branches scattered all over the place.  Looks like most of the warnings west of Barrie have been lifted.  Crazy stuff!
All calm now in Dufferin County (Mansfield) Going out to check the property for damage !
Big downpour in Whitby now.....
More from Angus.
Holy ****

Yup, something did some really bad damage out that way.  I just took a drive, trees down everywhere, branches scattered all over the place.  Looks like most of the warnings west of Barrie have been lifted.  Crazy stuff!  Ya,but calling for the same for Wednesday Bill.  Every time these things come through,it scares the crap out of me. Being on the hill,Im not sure if a tornado would happen. But know in the valley,it can happen .
Pay attention guys, it could get nasty over your way..
Supposedly there was a report of one on the ground in Walkerton not long ago. That series of cells just went through my dad's area around Fergus.
We have had some good rains and wind some what Lew.  Seems calm right now.  Im always keeping an eye on the sky here.  Your in an area that could see some bad weather as well  Stay safe all.
Hope the power doesn't go out. I'm watching footy.
Dark now here at 4:50pm,not looking good

Hope the power doesn't go out. I'm watching footy.   I was thinking about loading up the tube after work. Nasty humide today at work. Cool off time Then heard the watch. Then thought thrill ride of a water funnel. NOT LOL  Hope alls is well at your pops Dave.
Shelbourne about an hour ago.
Raf lives close.  Hope alls well with him as well.
That's a scary picture Dave, hope it's all good for your Dad.
I'm sure all is good Lew. We survived the 1996 one that was coming straight for our house before turning left in the farm field beside us.

What looks like clearing is about to start,then black and down pours.Then stops as fast as it starts,then back again.  I can remember fishing Little lake 20 some years ago. There was this black cloud that would circle around. Sun then rain then sun again then a down pour.  Are we in a vortex here? LOL

I'm sure all is good Lew. We survived the 1996 one that was coming straight for our house before turning left in the farm field beside us.  Good to hear Dave, I remember the big one that hit Barrie years ago and killed...I think...18 people.

Good to hear Dave, I remember the big one that hit Barrie years ago and killed...I think...18 people.  Yeah, that one was in the 80's and before it made it to Barrie it went down the main street in Grand Valley where we lived during the 96 tornado.
Pretty wild up here , NW of Alliston  !
I've never personally seen a tornado and hopefully, it stays that way.
